## Create repo on GitHub; add collaborators
GitHub -> set up New Repo
Add gitignore, e.g., Python
Add license, e.g., 3-clause BSD
Go to repo settings wheel -> collaborators -> add collaborators
Collaborators will need to accept the invitation by logging into their accounts

## Connect to repo as a collaborator
Local Computer -> C:\Users\USERNAME\Documents\GitHub
Run Git Bash from context menu
Otherwise need to navigate via cmd (use cd C:\)
Git Bash
$ git clone https://github.com/ACCOUNTNAME/REPONAME.git

## Add to GitHub desktop
GitHub Desktop -> add the newly added local GitHub folder